Adjust broiler rack so that it is in position closest to flame and place a #baking sheet{} on rack. Preheat broiler to high. Rinse @chicken cutlets{10%ounce}, then pat dry with a #paper towel{}. Season all over with @salt{} and @Tuscan heat spice{1%tablespoon}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add chicken and cook until browned and no longer pink in center, about ~{2%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and let cool slightly, then cut into bite-size pieces.

Wash and dry all produce. Cut any large @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces. Core, seed, and dice @Roma tomato{1}(diced). Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add broccoli and tomato. Cook, stirring, until just tender and wilted, about ~{3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Scatter @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup} in an even layer over @flatbreads{2}, followed by chicken, broccoli, and tomato. Carefully remove baking sheet from broiler and sprinkle with a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Place flatbreads on sheet and sprinkle each with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}.

Carefully return sheet to broiler and broil flatbreads until cheese melts and crust starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Check flatbreads occasionally for any burning.

Remove flatbreads from broiler. Sprinkle with another drizzle of @olive oil{} and season with @salt{}, if desired. Let flatbreads rest for ~{1%minute}, then cut into slices and serve.